00:00:07.830 --> 00:00:11.840
And I look after our business
in Middle East and Africa.

00:00:11.840 --> 00:00:16.530
Here today, we have an exciting
panel of really cool panelists

00:00:16.530 --> 00:00:18.120
from game companies
that have all

00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:21.310
had significant launches
in the last year or so.

00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:24.120
And we wanted to pick
their brain a little bit

00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:27.750
and learn from your experiences
over the last year on how

00:00:27.750 --> 00:00:30.900
you really took risk
off your game launches

00:00:30.900 --> 00:00:32.520
and improved its
initial performance

00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:36.600
by really developing at
scale, and then launching

00:00:36.600 --> 00:00:38.880
once you're ready, and
finding that right balance

00:00:38.880 --> 00:00:43.740
between a good launch strategy,
a good production cycle.

00:00:43.740 --> 00:00:46.950
We figured that developing
and launching games today

00:00:46.950 --> 00:00:49.830
is becoming an increasingly
expensive proposition

00:00:49.830 --> 00:00:52.020
and development costs
have been skyrocketing,

00:00:52.020 --> 00:00:54.000
you need to launch
with a good story line,

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.419
with proven mechanics,
with amazing graphics.

00:00:56.419 --> 00:00:58.710
And at the same time, you
need to appeal to an audience

00:00:58.710 --> 00:01:02.670
with a shortening attention
span, increased acquisition

00:01:02.670 --> 00:01:08.670
cost, and real high expectations
for high quality games.

00:01:08.670 --> 00:01:11.610
So, all in all, it's
becoming much more

00:01:11.610 --> 00:01:15.380
tricky to launch a hit, and
to launch a success upfront,

00:01:15.380 --> 00:01:17.860
yet there is a couple of
other tools and learnings

00:01:17.860 --> 00:01:20.970
you can really leverage
to understand early

00:01:20.970 --> 00:01:24.300
where your strengths lie
and where to best process

00:01:24.300 --> 00:01:26.749
with the game in order
to ensure the best

00:01:26.749 --> 00:01:28.290
possible success
once you're actually

00:01:28.290 --> 00:01:30.890
ready for a global
production launch.

