game, came out two weeks ago.

00:09:20.500 --> 00:09:24.280
And there was really two
phases during the soft launch.

00:09:24.280 --> 00:09:27.280
The first phase was OK, does
this have the retention metrics

00:09:27.280 --> 00:09:30.400
that we need to have a
successful game long term?

00:09:30.400 --> 00:09:33.421
That was something we looked
at between January and April.

00:09:33.421 --> 00:09:35.420
And because we had a
previous hidden object game

00:09:35.420 --> 00:09:37.030
before that was
a big success, we

00:09:37.030 --> 00:09:40.070
could compare apples to
apples and we saw very early,

00:09:40.070 --> 00:09:41.570
OK this will work.

00:09:41.570 --> 00:09:42.890
Retention is good.

00:09:42.890 --> 00:09:45.790
But then we had another six
month period, from April

00:09:45.790 --> 00:09:49.900
to October, where it was really
about de-risking the launch

00:09:49.900 --> 00:09:53.000
because life operations and
content are so critical.

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:56.500
So it's our highest
production value game ever.

00:09:56.500 --> 00:09:58.960
It's our biggest content
effort game ever.

00:09:58.960 --> 00:10:00.290
It's pretty ridiculous.

00:10:00.290 --> 00:10:03.660
So we release a new
chapter every single week,

00:10:03.660 --> 00:10:04.820
every Friday.

00:10:04.820 --> 00:10:09.270
And every chapter is
1600 man hours of work.

00:10:09.270 --> 00:10:11.150
So every Friday,
there's basically

00:10:11.150 --> 00:10:14.030
a chapter that would
take 40 people 40 hours

00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:17.080
a week to produce
every single Friday.

00:10:17.080 --> 00:10:19.310
With people internally,
with outsourcing,

00:10:19.310 --> 00:10:23.540
and it's ridiculous, but
we think it will work.

00:10:23.540 --> 00:10:26.080
The first two weeks of data
indicate that this will work.

00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:29.600
Our previous hidden object game
indicates that that will work.

00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:31.910
We really needed
the preparation time

00:10:31.910 --> 00:10:34.370
because we have an
author team, a writing

00:10:34.370 --> 00:10:36.020
team of three authors.

00:10:36.020 --> 00:10:37.786
They write about
a year in advance.

00:10:37.786 --> 00:10:39.410
So they are currently
writing the story

00:10:39.410 --> 00:10:42.490
that will appear in the game
in one year, next October.

00:10:42.490 --> 00:10:44.540
There's graphic production
in between, etc.

00:10:44.540 --> 00:10:48.680
So what we really did is we went
to the UK and we did something

00:10:48.680 --> 00:10:50.270
